Review from Amzon:&quot;This book was truly a great read! It's novella length, but don't let that fool you. (I'm already into book 3, by the way, and so far it's a great series). The love story is really true to life, with the main character, Rochelle, torn over her best friend, Elijah. Is he just a friend? She wants more, or does she? Also, Rochelle is a great female lead. Smart and intelligent. Finally a female character that isn't stupid! I read a lot of books, so I choose carefully what gets my time. The dialogue is smart, and the story really pulls you in. (Especially if you like Paris!). I recommend this book to anyone who likes a romantic series that doesn't follow the typical &quot;formula&quot; you get over and over with other romance books. A must read!&quot;
